.TH "libnvmf_context_set_reconnect_policy" 9 "libnvmf_context_set_reconnect_policy" "June 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
libnvmf_context_set_reconnect_policy \- Set reconnect policy for context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" libnvmf_context_set_reconnect_policy
.BI "(struct libnvmf_context *fctx "  ","
.BI "int ctrl_loss_tmo "  ","
.BI "int reconnect_delay "  ","
.BI "int fast_io_fail_tmo "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fctx" 12
Fabrics context
.IP "ctrl_loss_tmo" 12
Controller loss timeout in seconds; negative means retry
indefinitely
.IP "reconnect_delay" 12
Delay between reconnect attempts in seconds
.IP "fast_io_fail_tmo" 12
Fast I/O fail timeout in seconds; negative disables it;
must not exceed \fIctrl_loss_tmo\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Convenience setter for the three coupled reconnect policy parameters.
\fIctrl_loss_tmo\fP and \fIreconnect_delay\fP are coupled: the kernel derives the
maximum reconnect attempt count from their ratio. \fIfast_io_fail_tmo\fP
controls how quickly outstanding I/O is failed while reconnection is in
progress.

Individual \fBlibnvmf_context_set_ctrl_loss_tmo\fP, \fB_set_reconnect_delay\fP,
and \fB_set_fast_io_fail_tmo\fP accessors are also available when only a
subset needs to change.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
